{
  "message": "fix(raptorq): rewrite OG/Twitter share images with Satori-safe patterns\n\nBoth opengraph-image.tsx and twitter-image.tsx were returning 0-byte\nresponses (HTTP 200 with empty body) because Satori silently crashed on\nunsupported SVG features:\n- .map() inside SVG elements (dynamic JSX)\n- SVG <text> with textAnchor attribute\n- <polygon> elements\n- strokeDasharray on SVG shapes\n\nRewrote both images using proven patterns from working OG images\n(e.g. /about which returns 277KB). Uses only Satori-safe SVG\nprimitives: circle, rect, path, line, defs/linearGradient.\n\nAlso fixed page.tsx metadata:\n- Removed explicit openGraph.images and twitter.images overrides that\n  were pointing twitter:image to the OG endpoint instead of the\n  twitter-image file convention\n- Updated all '0.02%' references to 'under 5%' in descriptions and\n  JSON-LD schema to match the article content correction\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
